an Desk is to develop a partnership between NCEP and the African Meteorological Services through data and product exchange and to create of a cadre of meteorologists who can use and apply NCEP products in their local and general area of interest The African Desk conducts three main programs Training Operations and Research The training program is managed jointly by NCEP the International Activities of the National Weather Service and the World Meteorological Organization The African Desk hosts two visitors at a time for 4 month periods arriving at staggered intervals of 2 months The Desk provides training in methods of climate monitoring and prediction The African Desk works closely with the CPC component of the USAID Famine Early Warning System products fews FEWS Project to put together products tailored to assess vulnerability in Africa related to food security and water supplies For further information about our African Desk please contact W Thiaw at mailto wthiaw ncep noaa gov wassila thiaw noaa gov Expert Assessments products african desk rain guidance index html Seasonal Rainfall Outlooks products african desk rainfall index html Seasonal Rainfall Assessment Ten Day Weather Summary products african desk 10 weather summary index html Ten Day African Weather Summary Monitoring and Data This table is used for layout purposes only Daily Analyses products african desk mrf fcst satellite html Current Animated Meteosat Imagery products fews analyses html Current Analyses Weekly and Ten Day Analyses products african desk gts index html Station Precip and Temperature Data for Africa products fews dekad gif Ten Day Meteosat Rainfall Estimates Weekly SST products african desk weekly sst wkpacific html Pacific Ocean products african desk weekly sst wkatlind html Atlantic Indian Oceans products fews ITCZ itcz html Ten Day ITCZ Position Monthly and Seasonal Analyses products african desk monthly meteo index html Monthly Global Fields data indices index html Monthly Atmosphe